			"locked": false,
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"text": "Procedural links originating from or pointing at the same point \non the circumference of an thing's symbol (rectangle or ellipse)\nconvey the semantics of the logical XOR operator. Conversely,\nprocedurallinks originating from or arriving at different points \non the circumference of a thing's symbol convey the semantics \nof the logical AND operator.",
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": "HBcKQd8HqwnC5FJPbZadg",
			"originalText": "Procedural links originating from or pointing at the same point \non the circumference of an thing's symbol (rectangle or ellipse)\nconvey the semantics of the logical XOR operator. Conversely,\nprocedurallinks originating from or arriving at different points \non the circumference of a thing's symbol convey the semantics \nof the logical AND operator.",
